Very easy and quick to make. It was a great hit - people ate it with pita chips and crudites. There was none leftover after the party and I made quite a lot.

Rating: 3
Delicious and smooth -- I may have underdone it with the hazelnut oil though, and overdone it with the cumin. A colorful, great snack with carrots and celery as well as with pita chips.

Rating: 4
I followed recipe exactly except that I may have added a bit more red peppers (used half of 500 ml jar), so it was thick and rich. I used panko bread crumbs. I served it as a dip with pita toasts, but it would also be delicious as an accompaniement to grilled meat or as a sandwich spread. My guests like it so much they took it to the dinner table after we were done with cocktails. No leftovers.

Rating: 4
Served this with pita chips and my guests loved it. I used quite a bit more cumin and also added some dried red pepper flakes. I agree that the addition of a bit of lemon juice really brightens all the flavors in the dip. Don't be tempted to cheat and use canned bread crumbs; the fresh crumbs really make the texture of this dip. A keeper for sure!

Rating: 4
This dip was very good. I served it with crudites at a Mother's Day picnic. Everyone enjoyed it. I added the juice of 1/2 a lime to brighten up the flavor. Would have used lemon juice, but didn't have a lemon.

